# Custom MongoDB logrotate cron entry.
#
# Redirect stdout+stderr to a known file so a CLEAN run leaves an EMPTY file,
# and a MISSING file becomes evidence the command never ran.
#
# The critical detail: the redirect MUST end in `2>&1`, not `2>&`.
#   2>&   -> shell syntax error; the line dies before logrotate runs (silent failure)
#   2>&1  -> stderr follows stdout into the log file (correct)
#
# Verify with:  crontab -l | cat -A     ( a correct line ends in  2>&1$ )

# Every Thursday at 17:30 UTC
30 17 * * 4 /usr/sbin/logrotate -f /etc/logrotate.custom/mongod > /tmp/mongo_rotate_error.log 2>&1
